<pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; main() {     int i;// OS provide space for integer "i" of integer size     int *pi = &amp;i; // OS provide space for pointer "pi" of integer size with initial value is "address of i"     scanf("%d", pi); // OS gives input to pointer "pi"     printf("%d\n", i+5); // printed value will be 5 more than value of "i" } </code></pre>  <hr>  <p>This program works fine <a href="http://cpp.sh/7fh4" rel="nofollow">here</a> .</p>  <blockquote>   <p>But why below line(input to program) value gives to the integer "i" ,   why not address of integer "i" ?</p>  <pre><code>scanf("%d", pi); // OS gives input to pointer "pi" </code></pre>      <p>Why doesn't give output "garbage" value or error in program ,   explanation needed ?</p> </blockquote>